- Australia: 50% CGT discount for assets held >12 months

**SBLOC Cost Model:**
Annual Interest = Loan Balance × (Reference Rate + Margin)
- Typical reference rate: SOFR (US), SONIA (UK), CORRA (Canada), BBSY (Australia)
- Typical margin: 1-2% above reference rate

**Margin Call Risk (LTV):**
- Maintenance Margin: 25-30% (Regulation T / standard broker requirements)
- Margin Call Threshold: When Loan Value / Portfolio Value > Maintenance Margin
- Liquidation Price = Loan Balance / (Shares × Maintenance Margin %)

**Net Wealth Advantage:**
Compounds the tax savings from avoiding liquidation over the analysis period.`,
