    methodology: `This calculator computes the Section 199A Qualified Business Income (QBI) deduction for pass-through entities (sole proprietors, partnerships, S-Corps).

**Base Deduction:**
QBI Deduction = 20% × Qualified Business Income

**W-2 Wage / UBIA Limitation (for specified service trades above threshold):**
Greater of:
1. 50% of W-2 Wages paid by the business
2. 25% of W-2 Wages + 2.5% of UBIA (Unadjusted Basis Immediately Acquired) of qualified property

**Income Thresholds (2024):**
- Single: $191,950 (full deduction below, phase-out starts)
- Married Filing Jointly: $383,900
- Phase-out range: $50,000 (single) / $100,000 (MFJ)

**SSTB (Specified Service Trade or Business):**
Fully disallowed above the upper threshold. Partially disallowed within the phase-out range.

**Eligible Businesses:**
Most trades and businesses qualify except: C-Corps, certain service businesses (health, law, accounting, consulting, financial services, athletics).`,
