    methodology: `This calculator computes the tax savings from realizing investment losses to offset capital gains, with country-specific wash sale and loss rules.

**US Tax Loss Harvesting:**
- Losses offset gains dollar-for-dollar
- Up to $3,000 of net losses can offset ordinary income
- Wash Sale Rule: Cannot repurchase "substantially identical" security within 30 days before/after sale
- Remaining losses carry forward indefinitely

**UK Capital Losses:**
- Losses offset gains in same or future tax years
- No limit on loss offset
- 30-day "bed and breakfasting" rule (cannot repurchase same security within 30 days)
- Losses must be reported to HMRC within 4 years

**Canada Superficial Loss Rules:**
- Losses denied if repurchase within 30 days before/after
- Superficial loss added to ACB of replacement shares
- Losses can offset gains + $2,500 of net capital losses
- Net capital losses carry forward indefinitely

**Australia Wash Sale Rules:**
