    blog: "/blog/mortgage-recast-us/",
    methodology: `This calculator computes the impact of making a lump-sum principal payment on your mortgage, including reduced monthly payments and total interest savings.

**US Mortgage Recast:**
- Standard amortization: M = P[r(1+r)^n]/[(1+r)^n-1]
- Where P = principal, r = monthly rate, n = remaining months
- After lump-sum: New M = (P - LumpSum)[r(1+r)^n]/[(1+r)^n-1]
- Typical recast fee: $150-$500
- Fannie Mae/Freddie Mac eligible loans can be recast

**UK Mortgage Overpayment:**
- Most lenders allow 10% overpayment per year penalty-free
- Overpayment reduces term OR monthly payment (borrower choice)
- Some lenders charge Early Repayment Charge (ERC): 1-5%
- Offset accounts available with some lenders

**Canada Mortgage Prepayment:**
- Standard prepayment privilege: 10-20% of original principal annually
- Prepayment penalty: Interest Rate Differential (IRD) or 3 months interest
- Lump-sum payments applied directly to principal

**Australia Home Loan:**
- Offset account: Interest calculated on net balance (loan - offset)
- Redraw facility: Access extra repayments if needed
- Split loans: Part fixed, part variable
- Comparison rate includes fees and charges`,
